  "description": "A probabilistic programming package for Bayesian statistical modelling in R using native R syntax. Models are defined interactively with 'gretaR_array' objects, then compiled to 'torch' tensors for GPU-accelerated Hamiltonian Monte Carlo and No-U-Turn Sampler inference. No Python dependency required.",
